      "id": "9af3299f-f64c-4676-bc23-f1684b34adfe",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Exhaustive & Backtracking search\n1. Exhaustive search\n- Explore all possible candidates --> check\n\n2. Backtracking search\n- Each candidate is the result of a sequence of decisions\n- If only some first decisions are made --> a partial candidate\n- Use the recursion to explore all partial candidates systematically\n- How to explore a given partial candidate: (pseudo code)\n    + No more decision to made --> a complete solution\n    + Otherwise:\n        + Take the next decision\n        + ",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "9af3299f-f64c-4676-bc23-f1684b34adfe"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "acfa32bf-7868-40d0-a9b8-2bdf22fecd0c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Example 1: Print all binary strings of length n\n\nExample: n = 3\n    000\n    001\n    010\n    011\n    100\n    101\n    110\n    111",
